  "text": "The Rust compiler's trait method candidate collection and ambiguity error reporting spans multiple modules across the type checking and trait selection systems.\n\n**Candidate Collection Phase:**\n\nThe primary file for collecting trait method candidates is `compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/probe.rs`. The `ProbeContext` struct (line 52) maintains both `inherent_candidates` and `extension_candidates` vectors. Trait method candidates are assembled through:\n\n1. `assemble_extension_candidates_for_traits_in_scope` (line 1011) - iterates through traits in scope and calls `assemble_extension_candidates_for_trait` for each\n2. `assemble_extension_candidates_for_trait` (line 1054) - for a specific trait, collects all applicable method candidates by iterating over `impl_or_trait_item` and pushing them via `push_candidate`\n3. `push_candidate` (line 781) - adds candidates to either `inherent_candidates` or `extension_candidates` list based on accessibility\n\nThe `consider_candidates` function (line 1676) is critical for the candidate selection logic. It filters candidates, removes unstable ones, attempts trait-to-subtrait collapsing, and at line 1741 returns `MethodError::Ambiguity(sources)` when multiple candidates remain applicable.\n\n**Ambiguity Error Reporting:**\n\nWhen ambiguity is detected, error reporting occurs in:\n\n1. `compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/suggest.rs`:\n   - `report_method_error` (line 145) handles the `MethodError::Ambiguity` variant at line 221, creating error code E0034\n   - `note_candidates_on_method_error` (line 2149) formats and displays the ambiguous candidate sources to the user\n\n2. `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/error_reporting/traits/ambiguity.rs`:\n   - `compute_applicable_impls_for_diagnostics` (line 31) collects applicable trait implementations for diagnostic purposes\n   - `maybe_report_ambiguity` (line 160) handles ambiguity reporting for trait obligations, producing error E0283\n\n**ICE Points:**\n\nInternal compiler errors related to trait candidate selection occur in `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/solve/select.rs`:\n\n1. Line 113 (in `candidate_should_be_dropped_in_favor_of`): `bug!(\"should not have assembled a CoherenceUnknowable candidate\")`\n2. Line 184 (in `to_selection`): `span_bug!(span, \"didn't expect to select an unknowable candidate\")`\n3. Line 194 (in `to_selection`): `span_bug!(span, \"didn't expect to assemble trait candidate from {:#?}\", cand.kind())`\n\nThese ICE points indicate unexpected states during trait candidate selection when the new trait solver encounters candidates that shouldn't have been assembled or selected."
}

